# Shared Types & API Contract Rules

## Core Principle
The backend FastAPI is the **single source of truth** for all API types.
Frontend TypeScript types are **auto-generated** from the OpenAPI spec.

## Workflow
1. Backend developer defines Pydantic schemas in `backend/app/schemas/`
2. FastAPI exposes `/openapi.json` automatically
3. Run `./scripts/sync-api-types.sh` to generate `frontend/src/lib/api-types.ts`
4. Frontend imports types from `api-types.ts` — never defines API types manually

## Rules
- `frontend/src/lib/api-types.ts` is AUTO-GENERATED — NEVER edit by hand
- If you need to change an API type, change the Pydantic schema in backend first
- After changing any backend schema, remind the user to run the sync script
- `shared/types/` may contain non-API types shared between front and back (e.g., enums, constants)

## API Client Pattern
```typescript
// frontend/src/lib/api.ts
const API_BASE = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL || "http://localhost:8000";

export async function apiFetch<T>(
  path: string,
  options?: RequestInit
): Promise<T> {
  const res = await fetch(`${API_BASE}${path}`, {
    headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json", ...options?.headers },
    ...options,
  });
  if (!res.ok) {
    const error = await res.json().catch(() => ({}));
    throw new ApiError(res.status, error.detail || "Unknown error");
  }
  return res.json();
}
```
